article.headline: Niagara 90, Liberty 81
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Charron Fisher scored 22 points leading Niagara to a 90-81 win over Liberty on Saturday. Niagara (17-11, 11-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) led 38-34 at halftime and took command of the game with a quick 7-1 outburst to start the second half. Clif Brown's field goal with 17:56 remaining made the score 45-35. Liberty (12-16, 6-6 Big South Conference) rallied with a 12-4 run through the middle of the second half. Dwight Brewington's free throw closed to within 66-60 with 7:57 left but the Flames could pull no closer than five points down the rest of the way. Larry Blair finished with 12 points for Liberty, leaving him just three points shy of the all-time scoring mark in the Big South Conference. Blair did set the conference's all-time field goals record in a game that tied for his second-lowest scoring output of the season. Brown finished with 18 points and 11 rebounds for Niagara, winners of six straight. Lorenzo Miles had 15 points. Alex McLean and Brewington each paced Liberty with 17 points. Anthony Smith finished with 15. Liberty has lost three-straight and fell to 1-11 on the road.
